<br>
Boy, this whole removing the flag idea is about the stupidest thing I have ever heard. What was the point in defeating those flag requirements if SoE was just going to water this expansion down? <br>
<br>
In doing this, Sony has not only trivialized 3/4's of the expansion, but also all the work me and my guildmates put into getting flagged. I am so glad that I wasted so much time and got myself killed so many times while getting or attempting HoH, CoD, PoTorment, PoNB, and PoTactics. Not to mention the countless BoT flaggings, and my 23 successful trials groups (this obviously doesnt count the 50-100 unsuccessful ones), for a flagging that I would've gotten trouble free in a due time anyway. <br>
<br>
I guess the whole idea of defeating events to advance just wasn't very popular, so SoE decided to give mine and my guilds (and every other player who put in the time to complete these events) accomplishments to everyone.<br>
<br>
The blame for this fucktarded-jackassularity does not fall on the RTA, this blame falls on every EQ player who rather than putting the time and effort into these events decided to complain about it. There are certain things in EQ that require time and effort; leveling, certain zones, AAs, and equipment. This game would not be fun if there was nothing to work towards, yet it seems with each patch they are dumbing this game down to the least common denominator.<br>
<br>
Congrats to everyone who complained and got access to every plane short of the elementals! At least I know that I got my flags the old fashioned way.... I earned them.<br>
